				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Like all dots, this spell is very good mana wise.  It deals much more damage than spirit strike and cost almost exactly the same amount of mana.  Because it's so slow, you cast it first on any monster before anything else.  I usually cast root, then this, then infectous cloud, then tainted breath.  Sometimes I throw in malise or insidious fever to lower resistances.  Then it's your choice when to charge into battle, you can keep on rooting and tainting until the monster is dead, or just use a few spirit strikes and frenzy yourself into battle.
				</font>
